text: Q24.| What would be the worst-case time complexity of the insertion sort algorithm, if the inputs are restricted to permutation of 1, 2...n with at most n inversion? (@) 6 (n?) (b) 6 (nlogn) (Â© 6 (n'9) (d) 6 (n) Solution: Worst time complexity of the insertion sort algorithm = number of elements + number of inversions = n+n=2n=0(n) Answer is D
